<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-18T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-18T17:00:00-05:00" n="583" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/1335: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                                </placeName> [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-18T16:00:00-06:00">February 18, 1932—4
                                p.m.</date>]<lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Conference between Government and Castristas now under way at Legation,
                            firing stopped at 1 p.m., and many Castrista troops have handed in arms.
                            Insurrection believed over. Further details later.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>